  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In addition to normal, linear playback, users also want the ability to seek or scrub in a nonlinear manner to quickly get to various points of interest within the media. AVKit automatically provides a scrubbing control for you (if supported by the media), but if you’re building a custom player, you’ll need to build this feature yourself. Even in cases where you’re using AVKit, you still may want to provide a supplemental user interface, such as a table view or a collection view, that lets users quickly skip to various locations in the media."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Jump to a Specific Time Quickly",
          "anchor": "2948489"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can seek in a number of ways using the methods of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avplayer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avplayeritem"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". The most common way is to use the player’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avplayer/1385953-seektotime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method, passing it a destination "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coremedia/cmtime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " value as follows:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "// Seek to the 2 minute mark",
            "let time = CMTime(value: 120, timescale: 1)",
            "player.seek(to: time)"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2948485",
            "title": "Listing 1"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avplayer/1385953-seektotime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method is a convenient way to quickly seek through your presentation, but it’s tuned more for speed rather than precision. This means the actual time to which the player moves may differ from the time you requested."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Jump to a Specific Time Accurately ",
          "anchor": "2948488"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If you need to implement precise seeking behavior, use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avplayer/1387741-seektotime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method, which lets you indicate the tolerated amount of deviation from your target time (before and after). If you need to provide sample-accurate seeking behavior, you can indicate that zero tolerance is allowed:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "// Seek to the first frame at 3:25 mark",
            "let seekTime = CMTime(seconds: 205, preferredTimescale: Int32(NSEC_PER_SEC))",
            "player.seek(to: seekTime, toleranceBefore: kCMTimeZero, toleranceAfter: kCMTimeZero)"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2948486",
            "title": "Listing 2"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Calling the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "seek(to:toleranceBefore:toleranceAfter:)"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " method with small or zero-valued tolerances may incur additional decoding delay, which can impact your app’s seeking behavior."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "important"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        }
      ]
    }
